HEADWORD: Xerophilous
<hw>Xe*roph"i*lous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>xhro`s</grk> dry + <?/ to love.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Drought-loving; able withstand the absence or lack of
moisture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Plants which are peculiarly adapted to dry climates are termed by
<person>De Candolle</person> <qex>xerophilous</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Goodale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Xerophthalmia</ent>⟦br⟧
